Preheat oven to 325째F (160째C) Rinse and wipe chicken with paper towel. Place breast-side down in a roasting pan. Stuff cavity with lemon and garlic. Slice leeks in half lengthwise. Place cut-side down in roasting pan alongside chicken. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Pour in 3/4 cup (175 mL) water (see Notes.) Cover tightly. Roast in preheated oven for 40 minutes. Remove from oven and transfer leeks to a dish and keep warm. Return chicken to oven. Continue roasting, uncovered, for about 1-1/2 hours or until meat thermometer registers 180째F (82째C). Remove chicken from oven. Let stand for 5 minutes before carving. Serve with leeks and any pan juices.